The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: Sudhir Vasudeva, head of offshore oil and gas fields of ONGC, was today selected to head the countrys most valuable state-owned firm by market cap. The governments headhunters  Public Enterprise Selection Board  selected Vasudeva, 56, to take over as chairman and managing director of Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC) after interviewing eight candidates, sources said.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: Essar group firm Aegis today forayed into Argentina by taking over BPO company Actionline, which has estimated revenues of over $50 million annually. This is the sixteenth acquisition for Aegis over the last five years.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: Direct tax collections rose 19 per cent to Rs 1,81,758 crore in the first half of the current fiscal compared with Rs 1,52,625 crore in the same period last year.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: SKF, the global supplier of rolling bearing and seals, will acquire US-based lubrication systems provider Lincoln Holdings Enterprises for $1 billion.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 19: SpiceJet today said Sun TV chief Kalanithi Maran and his firm KAL Airways had bought an additional 2.28 per cent equity for Rs 43.58 crore as part of the June deal to acquire 37.7 per cent stake in the carrier.
                                                                                                                          
